whyThisMatters:
class ClassName:
  def __init__(self, params):
    self.attr = value
obj = ClassName(args) — __init__ runs when you create an object. self refers to the object itself.

class Dog:
    species = 'Canis'  # class var — shared by all dogs
    def __init__(self, name):
        self.name = name  # instance var — unique per dog
Access class var: Dog.species or self.species. Instance var: self.name only.

